default4.default              defaultHow effectively do Community Transport services address the needdefaults of passengers in isolated communities? How could Community Transport be improved?default4.1default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOur Network and local transport providers have worked in partnership for many years to develop tried and tested solutions for individual communities, including demand respo
defaultnsive buses, community mini-buses, car-based taxis, good neighbour schemes and even community rail partnerships. This includes work with isolated communities. 
defaultEssex County Council supports 12 community transport schemes across Essex run as charitable organ
defaultisations.  The quality of service is
default a success due to it
default being personalised, flexible and reliable.
default4.2default              
defaultThe most recent CTA State of the Sector Report showed the community transport sector is increasing but that some organisations
default were struggling 
defaultfinancially.  We believe that it will always need a degree of subsidy and
default/
defaultor grant funding to make a significant difference on rural routes.
